## 7. Code architecture

The pipeline is packages under `code/`, split so that **detection** knowledge and **library**
(technique) knowledge never bleed into each other; they only meet in `graph/`.

| Package | Role | Modules |
|---|---|---|
| `core/` | shared substrate | `canonical.py` (token → IAM permission) · `corpus.py` (locate the vendored corpora) · `normalize.py` (permission ⇢ `service.resource.verb`, used by capabilities) |
| `reference/` | pinned naming tables | `fetch_reference.py` (pin iam-dataset) · `rpc_methods.json` (curated gRPC table) |
| `detection/` | the **detection** side | `record.py` (the DNF record contract) · `parse_{sigma,elastic,gsecops,panther}.py` · `aggregate.py` (merge → `data/detections.json`) · `logtype.py` (Admin-Activity vs Data-Access) |
| `library/` | the **library** side | `parse_techniques.py` (→ `data/techniques.json`) · `capabilities.py` (GRANTS/IMPLIES/UNLOCKS) |
| `graph/` | assembly + analysis | `build_graph.py` (DNF join, load Neo4j, derive `DETECTED_BY` + `ENABLES`) · `run_queries.py` (`queries/*.cypher` → `out/findings.*`) |

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph REF["reference/ + data/reference/"]
    RM["method→permission tables (pinned)"]
  end
  subgraph DET["detection/"]
    SR["4 rule corpora"] --> PP["parse_* + aggregate"] --> DJ["data/detections.json"]
  end
  subgraph LIB["library/"]
    HT["hacktricks techniques"] --> PT["parse_techniques"] --> TJ["data/techniques.json"]
  end
  RM -. canonicalise .-> PP
  DJ --> BG["graph/build_graph"]
  TJ --> BG
  BG --> DB[("Neo4j")]
  DB --> RQ["graph/run_queries"] --> OUT["out/findings.{md,json}"]
  LT["detection/logtype"] -. log tier .-> BG
  CAP["library/capabilities"] -. chaining .-> BG
```

Each stage runs as a module (`python -m detection.aggregate`, `-m graph.build_graph`, …);
`run.sh` orchestrates the chain (`./run.sh`, `./run.sh analyze`, `./run.sh refresh`). The
corpora are not vendored — set `IAMOUFLAGE_CORPUS` / `--corpus-root` (default
`../../../draft/data/detections`).

